- Angular Framework by default supports form validations.

- if any error raised in form , automatically error stored into "$error"
  object.

- $error is the predefined object used to store the errors(form related errors).


Syntax:

    "form_logical_name".
    "form_element_logical_name".
    $error.
    "type_of_error"

Ex.

<form name="my_form">
    <label>Uname.</label>
    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="7"
           required>
    <div ng-if="my_form.uname.$error.minlength">
        ***Minimum 3 characters are required***
    </div>

    <div ng-if="my_form.uname.$error.maxlength">
        ***maximum 7 characters are allowed***
    </div>

    <div ng-if="my_form.uname.$error.required">
        ***Can't Left Blank***
    </div>
</form>


Ex. email validation
--------------------

<form name="myForm">
    <label>Email.</label>
    <input type="email"
           name="uemail"
           required>

    <div ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.email">***Please enter the valid email***.</div>
</label>


Ex. number validations
----------------------
<form name="myForm">
    <label>Phone.</label>
    <input type="text"
           name="uphone"
           ng-pattern="/^[0-9]{10,10}$/;"
           required>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.pattern">***Please enter the valid phone number***</div>
</form>

validations by using ngMessages module
--------------------------------------

 - ngMessages is the predefined module used o handle the form validations.
 - by using "ngMessages module" we can overcome the data redundancy.


Step 1:
    download ngMessages module by using bower.

Step 2:
    add the "ngMessages" dependency

step 3:
    create the validation messages with "ng-message" directive in external
    template

step 4:
    import the validation messages from external template
    by using ng-messages directive.
















